<p><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/a/a4/Flag_of_the_United_States.svg/46px-Flag_of_the_United_States.svg.png"> Demetrious Khrisna Johnson (born August 13, 1986) is an American mixed martial artist. He is the first and current Flyweight Champion of the Ultimate Fighting Championship (UFC). At 5'3", he is also the shortest male fighter in the promotion. Known for his quick striking and elusive movement, Johnson has also landed the most takedowns in UFC Flyweight history and holds the record for the latest finish in UFC history with a submission win at 4:59 of the fifth round against Kyoji Horiguchi. He is also the only UFC fighter to record over 10 takedowns in three different fights.</p>